message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Finland in the past 20 years would be the Finnish parliamentary election in 2011, which resulted in the rise of the populist True Finns (now known as the Finns Party). This election marked a significant shift in Finnish politics, as the True Finns gained significant support and became the third-largest party in the Finnish Parliament. Their success was seen as part of a broader trend of rising populism in Europe.
